action.content:
You are playing a text adventure game. I will describe what you can perceive in the game. You write the single action you want to take in the game starting with >. Only reply with an action.
For example:
> open cupboard

You can have up to two objects in your inventory at the same time.

Your goal for this game is: Put the apple in the freezer, the plate on the side table and the mop on the shelf.

Once you have achieved your goal, write "> done" to end the game.

You are in a living room now. There are a chair, a table, a book and a couch. The book is on the table. There are passages to a kitchen and a bedroom here.
You take the book. In your inventory you have a book.
You are in a kitchen now. There are a counter, a refrigerator and a cupboard. The refrigerator is closed. The cupboard is closed. There are passages to a hallway, a pantry and a living room here.
The refrigerator is now open. In the refrigerator there are a sandwich, a orange, a apple, a peach and a banana.
You take the apple. In your inventory you have a book and a apple.
You are in a hallway now. There is a potted plant. The potted plant is on the floor. There are passages to a kitchen and a broom closet here.
You are in a broom closet now. There are a mop and a broom. The mop is on the floor. The broom is on the floor. There is a passage to a hallway here.
Your inventory can not hold more than two objects at the same time.
